# Benchmark conventions

Plan: `docs/superpowers/plans/2026-05-14-benchmarks-and-simulations.md`

## Before timing

1. Shared `params.toml` across li and reference impls (C++, Rust, Julia, Python)
2. `verify.py` must pass (energy drift, momentum, trajectory hash)
3. **`lic build` must pass Lean** on all `benchmarks/tier2_physics/` li sources
4. Document flags: `lic --release --verified`, Clang `-O3 -march=native`

## Tiers

| Tier | Examples |
|------|----------|
| 0 | compile-time shape traps |
| 2 | `three_body`, `md_lennard_jones`, PDE stencils |
| 3 | `mlp_forward`, MNIST subset |

## Reporting

- CSV columns: `benchmark, lang, threads, metric, value, unit, cpu_model, flags`
- Label BLAS/NumPy/PyTorch columns explicitly — never compare naive Python to SIMD li without labeling
- Regression: investigate if li > 1.2× C++ on Tier 1–2 on the same machine

## Reference impls

Each Tier 2+ benchmark needs a C++ reference that passes `verify.py` before li numbers are published.
